Multimeter cross-check (Pro'sKit MT-1236, DC volts) on GROVE Port.A 5V vs GND:
  boost disabled: 0.7 V   (rail off; agrees with ADC 5VOUT near 0)
  boost enabled:  5.095 V, then 5.167 V on re-measure (see 20260531-m5pm1-5vout-meter.jpg)
ADC 5VOUT ~5.13 V vs meter 5.167 V: about 37 mV (~0.7%) agreement.
VBAT/VIN held steady throughout: no brownout, system rails untouched.
